35. HTML DOM

DOM = Document Object Model

Browser converts HTML into tree structure.

Example:

html
 ├── head
 └── body
      ├── h1
      └── p

JavaScript interacts with DOM.

36. HTML Validation

Validation checks syntax correctness.

Common errors:

Missing closing tags
Improper nesting
Duplicate IDs
Missing alt attributes
37. HTML Best Practices
Use semantic tags.
Write clean indentation.
Use lowercase tags.
Add alt attributes.
Avoid inline CSS.
Use meaningful class names.
Validate HTML.
Keep structure organized.
Ensure accessibility.
Optimize SEO.
38. Deprecated HTML Tags

Avoid using:

<font>
<center>
<big>
<strike>
<frameset>
<frame>
<acronym>
<tt>
<basefont>

Use CSS instead.

39. HTML Character Encodings

